-- Amplifon New Shares to Be Priced `Close to Market;' Stock Slides in Milan
-- B y   F r a n c e s c a   C i n e l l i   a n d   S a r a h   J o n e s
-- 2010-11-04T07:56:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-04/amplifon-new-shares-to-be-priced-close-to-market-level-term-sheet-shows.html
Amplifon SpA ’s new shares will be
priced “close to market,” according to terms of the sale
obtained by Bloomberg News.  The offer in an accelerated book-building process consists
of up to 19.84 million new shares, or 10 percent of current
share capital excluding subscription rights, according to the
terms.  Citigroup Inc. is acting as sole global coordinator and
joint bookrunner along with Banca IMI SpA, BNP Paribas SA and
UniCredit Corporate & Investment Banking, the company said in a
statement yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Francesca Cinelli  in Milan at 
 fcinelli@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Merritt at   dmerritt1@bloomberg.net  